I've been struggling with sleep for quite a while, but taking a class this week brought attention to how important it is to truly recognize and embrace my struggle and do something about it. The center of the class was the book "Why we Sleep" by Matthew Walker which has been on my reading list, but now needs to float to the top.
Wonderful as always Amy! Thank You so much!

Focusing on fixing sleep - esp. working on consistency of going to bed and awaking and being mindful of screen time. And I've been taking moments to play the piano - this relaxes me and tunes my mind. Its not the same as full-on practicing. It's just taking a few minutes to play music and feel the physical connections.

I feel completely supported during practice. I have been given particular "Phase 1" exercises to do and several of my required exercises are already included in our yoga practice. I have been adding yoga elements that I feel comfortable doing that I believe support the exercises, but always mindful of the limits these "Phase 1" exercises impose. I have my first in person OT/PT appointment on Tuesday. I am grateful to be back for weekly yoga!
Thank you so much Amy for sharing your Yoga Practice with me today. Always lovely.
I found linking breathing with movements to be very supportive. As always, Amy's encouragements to adapt to what feels best makes the practice personally supportive.

Thank you Amy for today’s practice. It was interesting how my joints were hurting right before you said what you were going to do for today’s practice. Thank you so much for sharing the practice that you did today, it was very beneficial.
I have exercises I'm doing in my post-surgery recovery that I can link yoga to and so I'm doing more and more yoga with my exercises.
Thank you so much for the lovely practice today! I loved it!
Thank you again Amy for all you have done for me, our community, and beyond!
I feel in tune with the changing season. It coincides with my transitioning to toward the next phase of my treatments. The changes feel right and timely.
Thank you so much for all that you do! You have helped me more than I can even place into words. You are a true blessing!

When I first pestered the court for us ladies (my peers) to have yoga I thought it was just going to be me and my peers and the yoga instructor only. Sidebar. I was in the hospital and I was asked by my team doctors if I wouldn’t mind another team to come and observe me. I granted it because that’s the type of person that I am. I said that to say that this is my time for myself. I would preferred not to be around anyone who has authority over me.  I would love everybody to be there male and female because Yoga is an excellent thing I’m finding out. But seriously I really wanted this to be just for the ladies who were in DWI Court to bond. They say this is anonymous but of course not today because I’m the only one who is actually a client of DWI Court who was in there today. For me I’m not getting the full relaxation because people in authority over me are in my space.  One last example. I get a massage every Thursday. To better explain the way I feel would be like someone from the courts showing up in my room while I’m getting my massage.  Thank you very much for the class or as I learn today for my practice. -dez
Thank you so much Amy for all of your love and support, and all that you have done for me. I feel so very grateful and blessed that we just happened to have crossed paths!
Linking breath and movement feels wonderful to me.
Thank you so very much for all that you do! You are the best! I am so very very grateful for you!
I appreciate you so very much! Thank you for sharing yoga with me today, and taking the to share with me! Have a lovely weekend!
I’m grateful for this time and I look forward to it weekly.

Following medical advice, I've consciously rested a lot this week. But I have also kept moving doing very gentle exercises and yoga this week. I have tried to stay positive. A head injury is scary - I don't see physical symptoms, but I know it is there and will take time to heal. Thank you for the very gentle practice today.
Thanks Amy for the practice today, and Happy Day Light Savings Weekend!

I have been practicing what I call "brain-resets" - throughout the day, I set a timer for 1 hour and every hour I try to rest for 10 minutes. I find that that slowing down feels good for my injured brain. Today's very relaxing practice was also a wonderful "brain-reset". Thank you.
Today I really enjoyed my practice.
Today's practice feels wonderful. I feel so reconnected head to toe.  thank you.
